    What is Joan Miró's most famous art piece?
    The Farm
    The Farm (1920–1922) is a vivid representation of Miró's Catalan heritage and one of his most famous works. This painting blends the precision of Cubism with a deep sense of personal symbolism.10 Jan 2025

    About

    Description

    Joan Miró i Ferrà was a Catalan Spanish painter, sculptor and ceramist. A museum dedicated to his work, the Fundació Joan Miró, was established in his native city of Barcelona in 1975, and another, the Fundació Pilar i Joan Miró, was established in his adoptive city of Palma in 1981. Wikipedia
    Born: April 20, 1893, Barcelona
    Died: December 25, 1983 (age 90 years), Palma
    Periods: Surrealism, Modern art, Dada
    Influenced by: Pablo Picasso, André Breton, Hans Arp, André Masson, Hieronymus Bosch, Tristan Tzara, Modest Urgell
    Children: María Dolores Miró
    Education: Cercle Artístic de Sant Lluc
